The Liberty corvette is a sturdy and powerful warship. It is the Lycentian go-to for routine patrols, station defense, and filling out a combat fleet.
The Edict corvette is a tough and agile warship. It is commonly used by the Kavani in patrol and rapid response roles.
The Knifejaw corvette is a solid and versatile warship. The Foralkan Armada makes extensive use of it in small, agile attack fleets.
The Chevron is a workhorse warship that makes up for its lack in agility with strength and stubbornness.

The Radix corvette has a radical design, giving it a significant speed advantage over ships of a comparable size. It is significantly less armored, in the hopes that its speed and maneuverability allow it to avoid damage altogether.

The Infinity is a corvette designed with a focus around rapid response, having a comparitively fast warp speed and charge time, as well as substantial damage and shield regen. However, its lack of overall hull and shield durability make it susceptible to melting under pressure.
The Sabre is a powerful fighter that makes up for its lack in speed with impressive firepower and tanking ability.
Based on the Aurora chassis, the Luminar is an advanced fighter whose heavy shields give it a distinct advantage in combat situations.
The Hybrid Claymore is a technological marvel, combining human engineering with advanced drone technology to create the ultimate tank of a fighter.
The Thresher is an upgraded variant of the  Piranha, serving the role of advanced fighter for the Foralkan Armada.
The Luster is a Lycentian fighter. This all-around ship is a step ahead of the Aurora which it is derived from.
The Aurora is a general-purpose fighter spacecraft that can perform well in a large array of situations.
The Claymore, an advanced upgrade of the successful Sabre fighter chassis, is a hull tanking machine with remarkably strong damage output.
The Hybrid Luminar is a technological marvel, combining human engineering with advanced drone technology to create a fighter with unparalleled shielding.
The Piranha is a Foralkan fighter based on the Sabre chassis. It is more nimble than the Sabre, though also cannot take quite as much of a beating during a fight.
The Lucent is an upgraded variant of the  Luster, serving the role of advanded fighter for the Lycentian Starfleet.
The Toucan is a Kavani fighter.
The Hornbill is an upgraded variant of the  Toucan, serving the role of advanced fighter for the Kavani Navy.
The Zenith is an agile starship developed to be able to hold its own in combat with normal fighters.
The Falcon is a swift starship designed for overtaking other ships in warp and having unmatched speed on the battlefield.
An advanced upgraded variant of the Falcon, the Paragon is one of the fastest and most agile ships in the galaxy.
The Polaris is an advanced upgrade of the Zenith design that generally improves upon its speed, offense, and defense.
The Hybrid Paragon is a technological marvel, combining human engineering with advanced drone technology to create the fastest interceptor in the known galaxy.
The Hybrid Polaris is a technological marvel, combining human engineering with advanced drone technology to create a remarkable fighter-interceptor.
The Parrot is a Kavani fighter based on the Falcon chassis. Though not quite as swift, this ship has a significant improvement in offense and defense from the Falcon.
The Macaw is an upgraded variant of the Kavani Parrot, serving the role of advanced interceptor for the Kavani Navy.
The Tetra is a Lycentian interceptor.
The Triazo is an upgraded variant of the  Tetra, serving in the role of advanced interceptor for the Lycentian Starfleet.
The Mackerel is a Foralkan interceptor.
The Candiru is an upgraded variant of the Foralkan Mackerel, serving the role of advanced interceptor for the Foralkan Armada.
The Marlin is a nimble vessel that is designed to mine efficiently but be capable of making a quick escape when necessary.
Seeing the need for higher rates of ore extraction, engineers improved upon the Otter design to create the advanced and more capable Badger.
The Honey Badger takes the ore extraction rate of the Badger and dials it up even further, creating a sturdy and extremely efficient mining ship.
An advanced upgrade of the Marlin, the Mako has an improved speed and mining rate over its predecessor.
The Ozark is a dedicated mining platform with the ability to quickly strip asteroid fields of ore using its considerable bonus to mining turret yield.

The Kodiak is a large mining platform capable of quickly stripping asteroids of ore. With two dedicated combat turret slots, the Kodiak can defend itself against threats which could otherwise interrupt its operation.
The Yukon is a giant mining platform which can effectively strip mine entire asteroid fields.
The Vesta is a large combined miner-hauler. While not as capable of a miner as the Kodiak, its cargo capacity allows it to sustain unaided mining expeditions for longer periods of time.
The Eos is a combined miner-hauler developed by the Trade Union. It is primarily intended for long-term unsupported mining expeditions.
The Koronis combines modest mining ability with the ability to haul cargo, allowing it to support itself on long-duration mining missions or take on multiple roles.
The Hyrax is an entry-level hauler. Though it lacks in both capacity and agility, it is a good step for someone looking to advance their career in cargo hauling.
The Rhino is a hauler designed with an emphasis on speed and agility over cargo capacity. This class of ship is designed for escortless pilots who are looking to make riskier cargo runs.

The Bison is a hauler designed to have a large cargo capacity at the expense of speed and agility. It won't outrun anything, but it can make you a fortune if you manage to make it to your destination.
The Zubron is a large hauling vessel. Unlike its smaller unarmed counterparts, it is able to defend itself through the use of two turret hardpoints.
The Shroud is a large and stealthy hauling frigate. It uses a combination of speed, low signal range, and adequate defenses to run blockades and evade dangerous encounters.
The Galaxy is a beast of a hauler, utilized by the Trade Union for transporting materials when danger is not of large concern. It is slow and cumbersome, but turns a hefty profit with each run.

The Veil is a stealth-focused hauling corvette. Although it has lower capacity than the Astero or Zubron, its high agility and low signal range make it ideal for hauling missions requiring speed and stealth.
The Astero is a large hauling corvette utilized by the Trade Union. While it leaves something to be desired in terms of agility, no ship in its class can outmatch its cargo capacity.
The Fargo is an entry-level vendor, a ship with the ability to sell items directly to other pilots through its onboard store.
The Yuma is a large vendor which has the capacity to place up to ten items on sale in its onboard store.
Like many Lycentian ships, the Virtue is a blocky (and thus sturdy) warship. It finds itself taking on many different roles in the Lycentian Navy.
The Judicator frigate is a formidable warship of the Kavani Navy. Its top-heavy turret placement allows it to go head-to-head with other ships in its class, despite its relative structural weakness.
The Barracuda is the frigate of choice for the Foralkan Armada. It is a well-rounded warship capable of filling many roles in a fleet.
The Phalanx frigate is a sturdy and stubborn warship. Though it doesn't handle movement particularly well, it is perfectly content sitting in place while devastating its enemies.
The Halo frigate, named for the iconic ring of its midsection, utilizes a lightweight construction that makes it significantly faster than other frigates.

The Adamant is a frigate designed with a focus around rapid response, having a comparitively fast warp speed and charge time, as well as substantial damage and shield regen. However, its lack of overall hull and shield durability make it susceptible to melting under pressure.
The Justice is a well-rounded and powerful warship, and the prized destroyer of the Lycentian Starfleet.
Keeping with tradition of Kavani design, the Conciliator destroyer is more agile (but less durable) than its counterparts produced by the other nations.
The Bulwark destroyer is a powerful, unyielding warship. It makes up for its lacking agility with immense firepower and defensive capabilities.
The Horizon is unusually agile for a destroyer. While it sacrifices firepower and durability, it can run laps around other ships in its class.
The Loxodon represents the Foralkan Armada's dedication to firepower, using its medium turret slots to great advantage.
The Echelon is a slow and sturdy beast of a warship, capable of withstanding an incredible amount of structural damage before yielding thanks to its redundant hull plating.

The Fortitude is a destroyer designed with a focus around rapid response, having a comparitively fast warp speed and charge time, as well as substantial damage and shield regen. However, its lack of overall hull and shield durability make it susceptible to melting under pressure.

The Liberty corvette is a sturdy and powerful warship. It is the Lycentian go-to for routine patrols, station defense, and filling out a combat fleet.

The Chevron is a workhorse warship that makes up for its lack in agility with strength and stubbornness.

The Radix corvette has a radical design, giving it a significant speed advantage over ships of a comparable size. It is significantly less armored, in the hopes that its speed and maneuverability allow it to avoid damage altogether.

The Infinity is a corvette designed with a focus around rapid response, having a comparitively fast warp speed and charge time, as well as substantial damage and shield regen. However, its lack of overall hull and shield durability make it susceptible to melting under pressure.
The Sabre is a powerful fighter that makes up for its lack in speed with impressive firepower and tanking ability.
Based on the Aurora chassis, the Luminar is an advanced fighter whose heavy shields give it a distinct advantage in combat situations.
The Hybrid Claymore is a technological marvel, combining human engineering with advanced drone technology to create the ultimate tank of a fighter.
The Thresher is an upgraded variant of the  Piranha, serving the role of advanced fighter for the Foralkan Armada.
The Luster is a Lycentian fighter. This all-around ship is a step ahead of the Aurora which it is derived from.
The Aurora is a general-purpose fighter spacecraft that can perform well in a large array of situations.
The Claymore, an advanced upgrade of the successful Sabre fighter chassis, is a hull tanking machine with remarkably strong damage output.
The Hybrid Luminar is a technological marvel, combining human engineering with advanced drone technology to create a fighter with unparalleled shielding.
The Piranha is a Foralkan fighter based on the Sabre chassis. It is more nimble than the Sabre, though also cannot take quite as much of a beating during a fight.
The Lucent is an upgraded variant of the  Luster, serving the role of advanded fighter for the Lycentian Starfleet.
The Toucan is a Kavani fighter.
The Hornbill is an upgraded variant of the  Toucan, serving the role of advanced fighter for the Kavani Navy.
The Zenith is an agile starship developed to be able to hold its own in combat with normal fighters.
The Falcon is a swift starship designed for overtaking other ships in warp and having unmatched speed on the battlefield.
An advanced upgraded variant of the Falcon, the Paragon is one of the fastest and most agile ships in the galaxy.
The Polaris is an advanced upgrade of the Zenith design that generally improves upon its speed, offense, and defense.
The Hybrid Paragon is a technological marvel, combining human engineering with advanced drone technology to create the fastest interceptor in the known galaxy.
The Hybrid Polaris is a technological marvel, combining human engineering with advanced drone technology to create a remarkable fighter-interceptor.
The Parrot is a Kavani fighter based on the Falcon chassis. Though not quite as swift, this ship has a significant improvement in offense and defense from the Falcon.
The Macaw is an upgraded variant of the Kavani Parrot, serving the role of advanced interceptor for the Kavani Navy.
The Tetra is a Lycentian interceptor.
The Triazo is an upgraded variant of the  Tetra, serving in the role of advanced interceptor for the Lycentian Starfleet.
The Mackerel is a Foralkan interceptor.
The Candiru is an upgraded variant of the Foralkan Mackerel, serving the role of advanced interceptor for the Foralkan Armada.
The Marlin is a nimble vessel that is designed to mine efficiently but be capable of making a quick escape when necessary.
Seeing the need for higher rates of ore extraction, engineers improved upon the Otter design to create the advanced and more capable Badger.
The Honey Badger takes the ore extraction rate of the Badger and dials it up even further, creating a sturdy and extremely efficient mining ship.
An advanced upgrade of the Marlin, the Mako has an improved speed and mining rate over its predecessor.
The Ozark is a dedicated mining platform with the ability to quickly strip asteroid fields of ore using its considerable bonus to mining turret yield.

The Kodiak is a large mining platform capable of quickly stripping asteroids of ore. With two dedicated combat turret slots, the Kodiak can defend itself against threats which could otherwise interrupt its operation.
The Yukon is a giant mining platform which can effectively strip mine entire asteroid fields.
The Vesta is a large combined miner-hauler. While not as capable of a miner as the Kodiak, its cargo capacity allows it to sustain unaided mining expeditions for longer periods of time.
The Eos is a combined miner-hauler developed by the Trade Union. It is primarily intended for long-term unsupported mining expeditions.
The Koronis combines modest mining ability with the ability to haul cargo, allowing it to support itself on long-duration mining missions or take on multiple roles.
The Hyrax is an entry-level hauler. Though it lacks in both capacity and agility, it is a good step for someone looking to advance their career in cargo hauling.
The Rhino is a hauler designed with an emphasis on speed and agility over cargo capacity. This class of ship is designed for escortless pilots who are looking to make riskier cargo runs.

The Bison is a hauler designed to have a large cargo capacity at the expense of speed and agility. It won't outrun anything, but it can make you a fortune if you manage to make it to your destination.
The Zubron is a large hauling vessel. Unlike its smaller unarmed counterparts, it is able to defend itself through the use of two turret hardpoints.
The Shroud is a large and stealthy hauling frigate. It uses a combination of speed, low signal range, and adequate defenses to run blockades and evade dangerous encounters.
The Galaxy is a beast of a hauler, utilized by the Trade Union for transporting materials when danger is not of large concern. It is slow and cumbersome, but turns a hefty profit with each run.

The Veil is a stealth-focused hauling corvette. Although it has lower capacity than the Astero or Zubron, its high agility and low signal range make it ideal for hauling missions requiring speed and stealth.
The Astero is a large hauling corvette utilized by the Trade Union. While it leaves something to be desired in terms of agility, no ship in its class can outmatch its cargo capacity.
The Fargo is an entry-level vendor, a ship with the ability to sell items directly to other pilots through its onboard store.
The Yuma is a large vendor which has the capacity to place up to ten items on sale in its onboard store.
Like many Lycentian ships, the Virtue is a blocky (and thus sturdy) warship. It finds itself taking on many different roles in the Lycentian Navy.
The Judicator frigate is a formidable warship of the Kavani Navy. Its top-heavy turret placement allows it to go head-to-head with other ships in its class, despite its relative structural weakness.
The Barracuda is the frigate of choice for the Foralkan Armada. It is a well-rounded warship capable of filling many roles in a fleet.
The Phalanx frigate is a sturdy and stubborn warship. Though it doesn't handle movement particularly well, it is perfectly content sitting in place while devastating its enemies.
The Halo frigate, named for the iconic ring of its midsection, utilizes a lightweight construction that makes it significantly faster than other frigates.

The Adamant is a frigate designed with a focus around rapid response, having a comparitively fast warp speed and charge time, as well as substantial damage and shield regen. However, its lack of overall hull and shield durability make it susceptible to melting under pressure.
The Justice is a well-rounded and powerful warship, and the prized destroyer of the Lycentian Starfleet.
Keeping with tradition of Kavani design, the Conciliator destroyer is more agile (but less durable) than its counterparts produced by the other nations.
The Bulwark destroyer is a powerful, unyielding warship. It makes up for its lacking agility with immense firepower and defensive capabilities.
The Horizon is unusually agile for a destroyer. While it sacrifices firepower and durability, it can run laps around other ships in its class.
The Loxodon represents the Foralkan Armada's dedication to firepower, using its medium turret slots to great advantage.
The Echelon is a slow and sturdy beast of a warship, capable of withstanding an incredible amount of structural damage before yielding thanks to its redundant hull plating.

The Fortitude is a destroyer designed with a focus around rapid response, having a comparitively fast warp speed and charge time, as well as substantial damage and shield regen. However, its lack of overall hull and shield durability make it susceptible to melting under pressure.
